# Agentic Patterns Playbook

This rule tells you **when** to reach for each of the 20 agentic design patterns and **what artifacts** must land alongside any AI-touching change. The living scorecard (current coverage, gaps, backlog) lives at **`docs/agentic-patterns.md`** — treat it as the source of truth for per-pattern status.

## When this rule applies

Apply whenever your change involves any of:

- An LLM call (OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, etc.) from app code, a script, or n8n.
- An n8n `@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent` node, a Router node feeding ≥2 AI branches, or any tool/vector-store node.
- A chain of ≥2 LLM-producing steps (even if some steps are non-LLM code nodes between them).
- Retrieval from a vector store, RAG corpus, or structured knowledge source feeding an LLM.
- Any human review step for AI-generated content (queues, approval UI, Slack sign-off).
- A new destination for AI output (email send, Slack post, LinkedIn publish, client deliverable).

If none of those apply, this rule is not relevant.

## Canonical 20 patterns (4 buckets)

The list is pinned in `docs/agentic-patterns.md`. Do not silently rename or drop entries — update the doc if the list evolves.

- **Grounding:** Prompt Chaining, Routing, Parallelization, Tool Use, RAG.
- **Transparent decision-making:** Planning/Orchestration, Chain-of-Thought, Tree-of-Thought, Multi-Agent Collaboration, Goal Tracking.
- **Self-awareness / QA:** Reflection, Debate, Self-Consistency, Learning & Feedback, Memory Management.
- **Production constraints:** Exception Handling, Human-in-the-Loop, Guardrails & Safety, Monitoring & Observability, Cost/Resource Control.

## Decision triggers — use the pattern when…

| Pattern | Reach for it when… |
|---|---|
| Prompt Chaining | A single prompt would have to do ≥2 distinct jobs (extract → transform → format). Split into named steps. |
| Routing | ≥2 downstream behaviors depend on a categorical input (diagnostic vs chat, lead source, plan tier, model tier). |
| Parallelization | Independent sub-tasks (multiple enrichments, multi-source research) can run concurrently with no shared mutable state. |
| Tool Use | The LLM needs fresh/authoritative data (DB, Supabase, Perplexity, Apify, Gmail) or deterministic compute (pricing, scoring). |
| RAG | The answer must cite or be grounded in project-specific docs, past meetings, evidence, or client-provided content. |
| Planning / Orchestration | Work spans ≥3 workflows/services with ordering or state handoff (e.g. the WF-000 → WF-012 client lifecycle). |
| Chain-of-Thought | Reasoning trace is valuable for auditability or debugging; capture it, don't just hope the model uses it. |
| Tree-of-Thought | Solution space has branches that are cheap to explore and prune (rare today — document why you need it before adding). |
| Multi-Agent Collaboration | One persona cannot hold all the responsibilities (researcher vs writer vs critic) without prompt bloat. |
| Goal Tracking | The agent runs across turns or steps and "am I done?" is non-trivial (diagnostic categories, lifecycle milestones). |
| Reflection | User-facing output ships without a human reviewer **and** low-quality output has real cost (outreach, client deliverables). |
| Debate | High-stakes classification or extraction where a single pass has unacceptable error rate and you have budget for N calls. |
| Self-Consistency | Same as Debate but with a single model — sample N times, take the majority / median. |
| Learning & Feedback | You collect outcomes (replies, conversions, ratings) and want prompts/workflows to improve over time. |
| Memory Management | Information must persist across turns (short-term: conversation window) or across sessions/agents (long-term: per-lead facts). |
| Exception Handling | Any network or LLM call; standard retry/backoff + curated user-facing error (see `no-expose-errors-to-users.mdc`). |
| Human-in-the-Loop | Any published artifact that leaves the building (outreach email, LinkedIn post, client deliverable, brand-facing copy). |
| Guardrails & Safety | New auth boundary, new user-facing error path, or new destination for AI output — content-safety + authz check required. |
| Monitoring & Observability | Any new agent step invoked in production — must emit `run_id`, `step_name`, `latency_ms`, token/$ cost. |
| Cost/Resource Control | Model tier, max tokens, and per-request budget cap must be explicit, not implicit in a prompt string. |

## Required artifacts when adding an agentic feature

Every PR that adds or modifies an agentic flow **must**:

1. **Declare patterns used.** In the PR description or plan, list which of the 20 patterns are present and why (one line each). Call out which ones you deliberately chose not to use.
2. **Update the scorecard.** Edit the relevant pattern section in [`docs/agentic-patterns.md`](../../docs/agentic-patterns.md): citations for "Where we use it today", adjust coverage rating if it changed, close/update backlog items.
3. **Name n8n nodes consistently** so the scorecard stays greppable:
   - AI agent nodes: `Agent - <Purpose>` (e.g. `Agent - Lead Research`).
   - Routers / IF nodes that choose between AI branches: `Router - <Decision>` (e.g. `Router - Diagnostic vs Chat`).
   - Tool nodes: `Tool - <Service>` (e.g. `Tool - Perplexity`).
   - Memory nodes: `Memory - <Scope>` (e.g. `Memory - Session Window`).
4. **Emit a monitoring event** for every new production agent step via the agent-run trace helper (ticket #1 in the scorecard; until it ships, call the cost-events ingest directly: [`app/api/admin/cost-events/ingest/route.ts`](../../app/api/admin/cost-events/ingest/route.ts)).
5. **Confirm HITL** for any path whose output reaches a client, prospect, or public channel. If HITL is intentionally skipped, justify it in the PR description.
6. **Set Cost/Resource caps.** Hard-coded model IDs are acceptable only if paired with a `maxOutputTokens` cap and a per-request budget check (or wrapped via the future policy router, ticket #5).

## Anti-patterns — do not ship these

- **Single-pass LLM for high-stakes output.** No reflection, no HITL, no self-consistency — reject.
- **Silent swallow of agent errors.** `catch {}` around an LLM/tool call without logging to cost-events or a trace. Reject.
- **HITL bypass on publish paths.** Any code that posts to LinkedIn / sends an outreach email / ships a client deliverable without a reviewed state must be justified in the PR and documented in the scorecard.
- **Hard-coded model IDs without env override.** `gpt-4o-mini` literal in business logic with no way to swap tiers. Move to config/policy.
- **Hidden chains.** Calling an LLM inside a "helper" that also does side effects (DB writes, emails). Split into pure chain steps so each is observable.
- **RAG with no retrieval quality signal.** If you add a new RAG path, add a way to evaluate top-k relevance (even a manual sample check recorded in the scorecard).
- **Memory without a bound.** Conversation windows without a size cap, long-term memory without TTL or tenant scoping.
- **Router without a default branch.** A router that can silently drop inputs it doesn't recognize.

